This paper discusses energy-efficient spectrum sensing and spectrum handoff in cognitive networks, which are primarily related to networking and information theory (cs.NI and cs.IT). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between energy consumption and throughput, which is a key consideration in cybersecurity (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the growth of high data rate applications, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
